	<ext_description linkend="Surface_conditions_mim"/>
	<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Surface_conditions_mim  Entity: contact_ratio_representation  
   <express_ref linkend="surface_conditions:mim:Surface_conditions_mim.contact_ratio_representation"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
	<ext_description linkend="Surface_conditions_mim.contact_ratio_representation">
A <b>contact_ratio_representation</b> is a type of <express_ref linkend="representation_schema:ir_express:representation_schema.representation"/> that represents the ratio of contact between an object and a measuring gauge. 
<p>For more information, see ARM definition of <express_ref linkend="Surface_conditions:arm:Surface_conditions_arm.Contact_ratio"/>. 
</p>
	</ext_description>
	<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Surface_conditions_mim  Entity: contact_ratio_representation  Where: WR1 
   <express_ref linkend="surface_conditions:mim:Surface_conditions_mim.contact_ratio_representation.wr:WR1"/>

  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
	<ext_description linkend="Surface_conditions_mim.contact_ratio_representation.wr:WR1">
Each instance of <b>contact_ratio_representation</b> shall contain exactly one <express_ref linkend="representation_schema:ir_express:representation_schema.representation_item"/> in its set of items. 
This <express_ref linkend="representation_schema:ir_express:representation_schema.representation_item"/> shall be of type <express_ref linkend="qualified_measure_schema:ir_express:qualified_measure_schema.measure_representation_item"/> or of type <express_ref linkend="Extended_measure_representation:mim:Extended_measure_representation_mim.value_range"/> and it shall have a name of 'ratio value'.
</ext_description>
	<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Surface_conditions_mim  Entity: contact_ratio_representation  Where: WR2 
   <express_ref linkend="surface_conditions:mim:Surface_conditions_mim.contact_ratio_representation.wr:WR2"/>

  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="Surface_conditions_mim.contact_ratio_representation.wr:WR2">
	Each instance of <b>contact_ratio_representation</b> shall be referenced as the 
	<express_ref linkend="product_property_representation_schema:ir_express:product_property_representation_schema.property_definition_representation.used_representation"/> 
	by exactly one 
	<express_ref linkend="product_property_representation_schema:ir_express:product_property_representation_schema.property_definition_representation"/> 
	that has a name of 'contact ratio reference'. 
	This 
	<express_ref linkend="product_property_representation_schema:ir_express:product_property_representation_schema.property_definition_representation"/> 
	shall relate the representation with a 
	<express_ref linkend="product_definition_schema:ir_express:product_definition_schema.product_definition"/>. 
</ext_description>
	<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Surface_conditions_mim  Entity: contact_ratio_representation  Where: WR3 
   <express_ref linkend="surface_conditions:mim:Surface_conditions_mim.contact_ratio_representation.wr:WR3"/>

  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
	<ext_description linkend="Surface_conditions_mim.contact_ratio_representation.wr:WR3">
Each instance of <b>contact_ratio_representation</b> shall be referenced by exactly one <express_ref linkend="product_property_representation_schema:ir_express:product_property_representation_schema.property_definition_representation"/>. 
This <express_ref linkend="product_property_representation_schema:ir_express:product_property_representation_schema.property_definition_representation"/> shall relate the representation with a <express_ref linkend="product_property_definition_schema:ir_express:product_property_definition_schema.property_definition"/> that is the <express_ref linkend="product_property_definition_schema:ir_express:product_property_definition_schema.general_property_association.derived_definition"/> of a <express_ref linkend="product_property_definition_schema:ir_express:product_property_definition_schema.general_property_association"/> that refers as <express_ref linkend="product_property_definition_schema:ir_express:product_property_definition_schema.general_property_association.base_definition"/> to a <express_ref linkend="product_property_definition_schema:ir_express:product_property_definition_schema.general_property"/>, which is a surface condition.
</ext_description>
	<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Surface_conditions_mim  Entity: hardness_representation  
   <express_ref linkend="surface_conditions:mim:Surface_conditions_mim.hardness_representation"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
	<ext_description linkend="Surface_conditions_mim.hardness_representation">
A <b>hardness_representation</b> is a type of <express_ref linkend="representation_schema:ir_express:representation_schema.representation"/> that represents the hardness of an object. 
For more information, see ARM definition for <express_ref linkend="Surface_conditions:arm:Surface_conditions_arm.Hardness"/>. 
</ext_description>
	<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Surface_conditions_mim  Entity: hardness_representation  Where: WR1 
   <express_ref linkend="surface_conditions:mim:Surface_conditions_mim.hardness_representation.wr:WR1"/>

  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
	<ext_description linkend="Surface_conditions_mim.hardness_representation.wr:WR1">
Each instance of <b>hardness_representation</b> shall contain between two and four <express_ref linkend="representation_schema:ir_express:representation_schema.representation_item"/> instances in its set of items. 
These <express_ref linkend="representation_schema:ir_express:representation_schema.representation_item"/> instances shall either be of type <express_ref linkend="qualified_measure_schema:ir_express:qualified_measure_schema.descriptive_representation_item"/> and have a name of either 'measuring method' or 'measuring position', or shall be of type <express_ref linkend="qualified_measure_schema:ir_express:qualified_measure_schema.measure_representation_item"/> or <express_ref linkend="Extended_measure_representation:mim:Extended_measure_representation_mim.value_range"/> and have a name of either 'depth' or 'hardness'. 
</ext_description>
	<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Surface_conditions_mim  Entity: hardness_representation  Where: WR2 
   <express_ref linkend="surface_conditions:mim:Surface_conditions_mim.hardness_representation.wr:WR2"/>

  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
	<ext_description linkend="Surface_conditions_mim.hardness_representation.wr:WR2">
Each instance of <b>hardness_representation</b> shall contain exactly one <express_ref linkend="representation_schema:ir_express:representation_schema.representation_item"/> in its set of items that has a name of 'measuring method'. 
</ext_description>
	<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Surface_conditions_mim  Entity: hardness_representation  Where: WR3 
   <express_ref linkend="surface_conditions:mim:Surface_conditions_mim.hardness_representation.wr:WR3"/>

  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
	<ext_description linkend="Surface_conditions_mim.hardness_representation.wr:WR3">
Each instance of <b>hardness_representation</b> shall contain exactly one <express_ref linkend="qualified_measure_schema:ir_express:qualified_measure_schema.measure_representation_item"/> or <express_ref linkend="Extended_measure_representation:mim:Extended_measure_representation_mim.value_range"/> in its set of items that has a name of 'hardness'.
</ext_description>
	<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Surface_conditions_mim  Entity: hardness_representation  Where: WR4 
   <express_ref linkend="surface_conditions:mim:Surface_conditions_mim.hardness_representation.wr:WR4"/>

  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
	<ext_description linkend="Surface_conditions_mim.hardness_representation.wr:WR4">
Each instance of <b>hardness_representation</b> shall contain at most one <express_ref linkend="representation_schema:ir_express:representation_schema.representation_item"/> in its set of items that has a name of 'measuring position'. 
</ext_description>
	<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Surface_conditions_mim  Entity: hardness_representation  Where: WR5 
   <express_ref linkend="surface_conditions:mim:Surface_conditions_mim.hardness_representation.wr:WR5"/>

  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
	<ext_description linkend="Surface_conditions_mim.hardness_representation.wr:WR5">
Each instance of <b>hardness_representation</b> shall contain at most one <express_ref linkend="qualified_measure_schema:ir_express:qualified_measure_schema.measure_representation_item"/> or <express_ref linkend="Extended_measure_representation:mim:Extended_measure_representation_mim.value_range"/> in its set of items that has a name of 'depth'. 
</ext_description>
	<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Surface_conditions_mim  Entity: hardness_representation  Where: WR6 
   <express_ref linkend="surface_conditions:mim:Surface_conditions_mim.hardness_representation.wr:WR6"/>

  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
	<ext_description linkend="Surface_conditions_mim.hardness_representation.wr:WR6">
Each instance of <b>hardness_representation</b> shall be referenced by exactly one <express_ref linkend="product_property_representation_schema:ir_express:product_property_representation_schema.property_definition_representation"/>. 
This <express_ref linkend="product_property_representation_schema:ir_express:product_property_representation_schema.property_definition_representation"/> shall relate the representation with a <express_ref linkend="product_property_definition_schema:ir_express:product_property_definition_schema.property_definition"/> that is the <express_ref linkend="product_property_definition_schema:ir_express:product_property_definition_schema.general_property_association.derived_definition"/> of a <express_ref linkend="product_property_definition_schema:ir_express:product_property_definition_schema.general_property_association"/> that refers as <express_ref linkend="product_property_definition_schema:ir_express:product_property_definition_schema.general_property_association.base_definition"/> to a <express_ref linkend="product_property_definition_schema:ir_express:product_property_definition_schema.general_property"/>, which is a surface condition. 
</ext_description>

	<ext_description linkend="Surface_conditions_mim.physically_modelled_product_definition">
A <b>physically_modelled_product_definition</b> is a type of <express_ref linkend="product_definition_schema:ir_express:product_definition_schema.product_definition"/> that provides a model of the shape of a part made from a certain material, like clay or wood, at a certain scale.
<example>
A <express_ref linkend="Surface_conditions:arm:Surface_conditions_arm.Physical_model"/> may be used to get an impression of the future appearance of a product.
</example>
	</ext_description>
	<ext_description linkend="Surface_conditions_mim.physically_modelled_product_definition.wr:WR1">
The <express_ref linkend="product_definition_schema:ir_express:product_definition_schema.product_definition.frame_of_reference"/> name shall be 'physical model occurrence'.
</ext_description>
	<ext_description linkend="Surface_conditions_mim.physically_modelled_product_definition.wr:WR2">
The <b>physically_modelled_product_definition</b> shall be a definition of a product of category 'document'.
</ext_description>
	<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Surface_conditions_mim  Entity: surface_texture_representation  
   <express_ref linkend="surface_conditions:mim:Surface_conditions_mim.surface_texture_representation"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
	<ext_description linkend="Surface_conditions_mim.surface_texture_representation">
A <b>surface_texture_representation</b> is a type of <express_ref linkend="representation_schema:ir_express:representation_schema.representation"/> that represents a surface texture such as roughness or waviness. 
The kind of surface texture that is represented is given in the names of the <express_ref linkend="representation_schema:ir_express:representation_schema.representation_item"/> instances. 
<p>The method or standard according to which the surface texture is represented is specified in the description of the <express_ref linkend="qualified_measure_schema:ir_express:qualified_measure_schema.descriptive_representation_item"/>. 
</p>
		<p>For more information, see ARM definition of <express_ref linkend="Surface_conditions:arm:Surface_conditions_arm.Surface_texture"/>. 
</p>
	</ext_description>
	<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Surface_conditions_mim  Entity: surface_texture_representation  Where: WR1 
   <express_ref linkend="surface_conditions:mim:Surface_conditions_mim.surface_texture_representation.wr:WR1"/>

  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
	<ext_description linkend="Surface_conditions_mim.surface_texture_representation.wr:WR1">
Each instance of <b>surface_texture_representation</b> shall contain only <express_ref linkend="representation_schema:ir_express:representation_schema.representation_item"/> instances that are of type <express_ref linkend="qualified_measure_schema:ir_express:qualified_measure_schema.measure_representation_item"/>, <express_ref linkend="Extended_measure_representation:mim:Extended_measure_representation_mim.value_range"/>, or <express_ref linkend="qualified_measure_schema:ir_express:qualified_measure_schema.descriptive_representation_item"/>. 
</ext_description>
	<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Surface_conditions_mim  Entity: surface_texture_representation  Where: WR2 
   <express_ref linkend="surface_conditions:mim:Surface_conditions_mim.surface_texture_representation.wr:WR2"/>

  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
	<ext_description linkend="Surface_conditions_mim.surface_texture_representation.wr:WR2">
Each instance of <b>surface_texture_representation</b> shall contain exactly one <express_ref linkend="qualified_measure_schema:ir_express:qualified_measure_schema.descriptive_representation_item"/>. 
The name of this <express_ref linkend="qualified_measure_schema:ir_express:qualified_measure_schema.descriptive_representation_item"/> shall be 'measuring method'. 

</ext_description>
	<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Surface_conditions_mim  Entity: surface_texture_representation  Where: WR3 
   <express_ref linkend="surface_conditions:mim:Surface_conditions_mim.surface_texture_representation.wr:WR3"/>

  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
	<ext_description linkend="Surface_conditions_mim.surface_texture_representation.wr:WR3">
Each instance of <b>surface_texture_representation</b> shall contain at least one <express_ref linkend="qualified_measure_schema:ir_express:qualified_measure_schema.measure_representation_item"/> or <express_ref linkend="Extended_measure_representation:mim:Extended_measure_representation_mim.value_range"/>. 

</ext_description>
	<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Surface_conditions_mim  Entity: surface_texture_representation  Where: WR4 
   <express_ref linkend="surface_conditions:mim:Surface_conditions_mim.surface_texture_representation.wr:WR4"/>

  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
	<ext_description linkend="Surface_conditions_mim.surface_texture_representation.wr:WR4">
Each instance of <b>surface_texture_representation</b> shall be referenced by at most one <express_ref linkend="representation_schema:ir_express:representation_schema.representation_relationship"/>. 
If such a relationship is present, the <b>surface_texture_representation</b> shall be the <express_ref linkend="representation_schema:ir_express:representation_schema.representation_relationship.rep_1"/> and the <express_ref linkend="representation_schema:ir_express:representation_schema.representation_relationship.rep_2"/> shall be a representation whose name is 'measuring direction'. 

</ext_description>
	<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Surface_conditions_mim  Entity: surface_texture_representation  Where: WR5 
   <express_ref linkend="surface_conditions:mim:Surface_conditions_mim.surface_texture_representation.wr:WR5"/>

  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
	<ext_description linkend="Surface_conditions_mim.surface_texture_representation.wr:WR5">
Each instance of <b>surface_texture_representation</b> shall be referenced by exactly one <express_ref linkend="product_property_representation_schema:ir_express:product_property_representation_schema.property_definition_representation"/>. 
This <express_ref linkend="product_property_representation_schema:ir_express:product_property_representation_schema.property_definition_representation"/> shall relate the representation with a <express_ref linkend="product_property_definition_schema:ir_express:product_property_definition_schema.property_definition"/> that is the <express_ref linkend="product_property_definition_schema:ir_express:product_property_definition_schema.general_property_association.derived_definition"/> of a <express_ref linkend="product_property_definition_schema:ir_express:product_property_definition_schema.general_property_association"/> that refers as <express_ref linkend="product_property_definition_schema:ir_express:product_property_definition_schema.general_property_association.base_definition"/> to a <express_ref linkend="product_property_definition_schema:ir_express:product_property_definition_schema.general_property"/>, which is a surface condition. 

</ext_description>
	<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Surface_conditions_mim  Entity: tactile_appearance_representation  
   <express_ref linkend="surface_conditions:mim:Surface_conditions_mim.tactile_appearance_representation"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
	<ext_description linkend="Surface_conditions_mim.tactile_appearance_representation">
A <b>tactile_appearance_representation</b> is a type of <express_ref linkend="representation_schema:ir_express:representation_schema.representation"/> that represents the tactile appearance of an object. 
<p>For more information see ARM definition of <express_ref linkend="Surface_conditions:arm:Surface_conditions_arm.Tactile_appearance"/>. 
</p>
	</ext_description>
	<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Surface_conditions_mim  Entity: tactile_appearance_representation  Where: WR1 
   <express_ref linkend="surface_conditions:mim:Surface_conditions_mim.tactile_appearance_representation.wr:WR1"/>

  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
	<ext_description linkend="Surface_conditions_mim.tactile_appearance_representation.wr:WR1">
Each instance of <b>tactile_appearance_representation</b> shall only <express_ref linkend="representation_schema:ir_express:representation_schema.representation_item"/> instances of type <express_ref linkend="qualified_measure_schema:ir_express:qualified_measure_schema.measure_representation_item"/> or <express_ref linkend="Extended_measure_representation:mim:Extended_measure_representation_mim.value_range"/> in its set of items. 
</ext_description>
	<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Surface_conditions_mim  Entity: tactile_appearance_representation  Where: WR2 
   <express_ref linkend="surface_conditions:mim:Surface_conditions_mim.tactile_appearance_representation.wr:WR2"/>

  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
	<ext_description linkend="Surface_conditions_mim.tactile_appearance_representation.wr:WR2">
At most one <express_ref linkend="qualified_measure_schema:ir_express:qualified_measure_schema.measure_representation_item"/> or <express_ref linkend="Extended_measure_representation:mim:Extended_measure_representation_mim.value_range"/> in the set of items shall have a name of 'depth'. 
</ext_description>
	<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Surface_conditions_mim  Entity: tactile_appearance_representation  Where: WR3 
   <express_ref linkend="surface_conditions:mim:Surface_conditions_mim.tactile_appearance_representation.wr:WR3"/>

