   <express_ref linkend="surface_conditions:mim:Surface_conditions_mim.visual_appearance_representation"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
	<ext_description linkend="Surface_conditions_mim.visual_appearance_representation">
A <b>visual_appearance_representation</b> is a type of <express_ref linkend="representation_schema:ir_express:representation_schema.representation"/> that representats the visual appearance of an object. 
<p>For more information see ARM definition of <express_ref linkend="Surface_conditions:arm:Surface_conditions_arm.Visual_appearance"/>. 
</p>
	</ext_description>
	<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Surface_conditions_mim  Entity: visual_appearance_representation  Where: WR1 
   <express_ref linkend="surface_conditions:mim:Surface_conditions_mim.visual_appearance_representation.wr:WR1"/>

  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
	<ext_description linkend="Surface_conditions_mim.visual_appearance_representation.wr:WR1">
Each instance of <b>visual_appearance_representation</b> shall contain between two and five <express_ref linkend="representation_schema:ir_express:representation_schema.representation_item"/> instances in its set of items. 
These <express_ref linkend="representation_schema:ir_express:representation_schema.representation_item"/> instances shall be of type <express_ref linkend="qualified_measure_schema:ir_express:qualified_measure_schema.descriptive_representation_item"/> and have a name of 'colour id', 'colour name', 'lustre', 'pattern', or 'transparency'. 
</ext_description>
